             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am a coach-maker: I am employed by Sir 
               <persName id="t17900526-4-person78">
                  William
                   Smith
               <interp inst="t17900526-4-person78" type="surname" value="Smith"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17900526-4-person78" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17900526-4-person78" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            ; his coach was in my shop; the hammer cloth was on it; it was missed the morning of the 20th of April; it was an oil-skin hammer cloth. Between eight and nine in the morning, my man, 
               <persName id="t17900526-4-person79">
                  Zachariah
                   Moore
               <interp inst="t17900526-4-person79" type="surname" value="Moore"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17900526-4-person79" type="given" value="Zachariah"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17900526-4-person79" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , brought the prisoner into my compting-house with the hammer cloth.</p>
               <p>(Produced and deposed to.)</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>A man employed me to fetch it, and promised me a shilling.</p>
